  "prompt": "Are there pens with thick grip and thinner tip?  Is it available in India below 50 rupees?",
  "response": "Yes, there are pens with a thick grip and a thinner tip available in the market. These pens are designed for individuals who prefer a more comfortable grip while writing, reducing strain on the fingers during extended writing sessions. \n\nIn India, several brands offer budget-friendly options that might fit your requirement of being priced below 50 rupees. While the prices and availability can vary based on the region and the store, here are a few brands you can look into:\n\n1. **Reynolds**: Known for its budget-friendly range, Reynolds often offers pens with ergonomic grips.\n   \n2. **Cello**: A popular brand in India that provides a wide variety of pens, including those with thicker grips.\n   \n3. **Linc**: Offers a range of affordable pens, some of which might have the combination of a thick grip and a thin writing tip.\n\n4. **Flair**: Known for innovative designs, Flair pens might have options that suit your needs under budget.\n\nTo ensure you find the right pen at the desired price, it would be best to visit a local stationery store or check online marketplaces like Amazon India or Flipkart. You can also look for any ongoing discounts or bulk purchase options that might bring the cost down.",
